==Description==
<div class="right-image">
[[File:Level0dot5.png|Ceaseless carpeted cubes.|500px|link=]] 
The first known image of '''Level 0.5''' posted by an unknown wanderer in 2019. The picture is undergoing an instance of [[Phenomenon_38|Sudden Unrealism]].
</div>
'''Level 0.5''' consists of a series of infinitely extending, randomly spliced solids. These solids have no uniform volume specifications — they range in size from small enough to be held in one hand to colossal blocks hundreds of meters in height. Moreover, these solids float above a sea of fog in a completely erratic manner, with the spacing between them varying from several meters to over a hundred meters.

The surfaces of all the solids within '''Level 0.5''' are completely covered by carpets in varying shades of blue, including indigo, sky blue, navy blue, cobalt blue and so on — with not a single area left exposed. The material of the carpets is similar to that of the carpets in [[Level 0]]. The difference, however, is that carpets within this level feel dry and slightly rough to the touch. Also, they do not absorb any dust or stains, and will not suffer any damage even when scratched with sharp objects.

Notably, the surfaces of the vast majority of '''Level 0.5'''<nowiki/>'s carpets are engraved with black linear patterns of varying thicknesses, which typically range from 1 millimetre to 3 centimetres in width and are approximately 2 millimetres in depth. All lines run strictly parallel to the edges of the solids they are on, with no tilting or bending whatsoever. Irregular gaps exist between these lines, and most of these gaps are rectangular or square in shape.

The composition of the solids within '''Level 0.5''' has thus far defied analysis by the [[M.E.G]] research team, as they exhibit such absolute indestructibility that no traces can be left on their surface even when subjected to high-temperature incineration, high-pressure impact, strong acid corrosion, and other such methods. It is hypothesized that the solids may be composed of a high-density metallic element unknown to humanity, and this metal has an extremely stable molecular structure, capable of withstanding even the corrosion of anomalous substances, though this hypothesis has yet to be empirically verified.

All solids within '''Level 0.5''' float above a boundless sea of light blue fog. The fog's color lies between sky blue and pale cyan, stretches infinitely outward and downward, and its end fades into the visual blind spot with no sign of any boundary or bottom. The fog is extremely dense, when wanderers are viewed at eye level from the surface of a solid, the visual range is no more than 30 feet; only the vague outlines of nearby solids can be seen, while distant scenery is completely swallowed by the fog. However, studies have shown that the density of the fog decreases as altitude increases; when wanderers climb to the top of taller solids, they will find that the surrounding fog has become relatively thin; although the fog never dissipates completely, it shrouds the entire level like a veil at all times. The light throughout the level comes from the fog’s faint, soft white fluorescence, and its brightness usually remains unchanged.

The fog of '''Level 0.5''' seems to be a mixture of water and [[Object 1|Almond Water]], but, though it retains the taste of [[Object 1|Almond Water]], the concentration of [[Object 1|Almond Water]] within the fog is incredibly small, making it necessary to inhale large amounts for the [[Object 1|Almond Water]] to begin having an effect. Also, it is only possible to inhale the fog while not on solid ground; when breathing on the surface of a solid, a formless barrier isolates the nasal cavity and oral cavity, and the composition of the inhaled gas is identical to that of normal air, and the principle behind this mechanism remains a mystery to this day.

Many objects can be found within '''Level 0.5''', mostly related to tabletop games, such as chess pieces, puzzle pieces, and dice. These objects can be picked up and carried normally, but their size varies with the observer's viewing angle — they appear in their regular size when viewed from the front; when viewed from the side or the back, they may shrink to the size of a thumb or expand to the size of a tabletop. Once the observer returns to the front viewing angle, the items will revert to their original size. It is worth mentioning that items brought into this level by wanderers from the outside world also exhibit the same perspective-dependent scaling effect, which indicates that the spatial structure of this level itself has the property of visual distortion.

The gravity rule on '''Level 0.5''' exhibits extreme anomalies: gravity acts only on the physical surfaces of solids, "adsorbing" wanderers on the contact surfaces. The magnitude of gravity is close to the gravitational acceleration on the Earth's surface, so there will be no discomfort caused by overweight or weightlessness. What's more peculiar is that no matter whether a wanderer is on the top, side, or bottom surface of a solid, they will perceive themselves as being on a "horizontal plane", and the direction of gravity always points to the surface under their feet. This characteristic allows wanderers to walk, run, and even jump freely on any side of a solid without worrying about falling.

However, in the gaps between the solids within '''Level 0.5''', gravity completely vanishes. Wanderers can float and move through the fog by their own strength, and even leap between solids. It should be noted that if a wanderer stays in the zero-gravity zone for more than 1 hour, fog dizziness and disorientation will occur, and these symptoms will become increasingly severe as the stay duration lengthens; whereas after returning to the surface of a solid, the symptoms will subside spontaneously within 10–20 minutes.

The time flow rule of '''Level 0.5''' is completely disordered, exhibiting a "discontinuous" characteristic — and this is one of the most dangerous features of the level. Wanderers will switch instantly from extreme hunger to a state of full satiety without any warning, even if they have consumed no food during this period; similarly, the states of thirst and quenched thirst alternate irregularly. Sometimes, one may feel a parched throat the very next second after drinking a large amount of water.

'''Level 0.5''' also distorts wanderers’ sense of time: one might feel as if they have only stayed for a few seconds, while hours have actually passed in reality; conversely, when they believe they have trekked for hours, the clocks they carry may have only ticked forward a couple of minutes. In addition, there is no day-night cycle at all on this level. Wanderers do not experience any sense of fatigue here, as the rate of their physical energy consumption is drastically slowed — they can walk continuously for dozens of hours without feeling tired. However, this only exacerbates their mental exhaustion.

What's more, within '''Level 0.5''', wanderers' sense of distance and direction is completely disrupted as well. When one attempts to travel in a straight line, their actual path will veer unconsciously, ultimately causing a severe deviation between the walking route and the intended one. Even if high-end instruments such as compasses and GPS locators are used, they cannot correct the direction, as the pointers of all these devices will malfunction and swing irregularly. As a result, it is impossible for wanderers to travel in a straight line within this level.

In addition to the above, prolonged stays in '''Level 0.5''' may also induce hallucinations. Multiple wanderers have reported seeing "the patterns of blue carpets flowing in the fog" during long-term exploration within this level, though this remains unconfirmed. It is speculated that the duration of hallucinations may be positively correlated with the length of time spent exploring the level.

==Entities==
There is only one native entity within '''Level 0.5''', codenamed "Qwerty".

===“Qwerty”===
<div class="fade-up-text">
<div class="CollapseContent">
{{Underline|d06e6e05}}
<div class="qwerty-text"><center>'''1010001 01010111 01000101 01010010 01010100 01011001'''</center></div>
{{Underline|d06e6e}}
<br>
In the pale blue fog of '''Level 0.5''' resides a mysterious and bizarrely shaped entity known as "Qwerty". Up to now, the [[M.E.G]] has not obtained complete morphological data on this entity. All witnesses have only been able to describe the parts of its limbs protruding from the mist, and no one knows what structure lies beneath the fog.

The observed Qwerty limbs consist of at least six slender, deep-blue appendages, each comparable in thickness to an adult male's arm and reaching lengths of up to dozens of meters. The surface is covered with short fuzz resembling the color of floor carpeting, giving a moist and slippery tactile sensation, with the fuzz gently swaying as the tentacles move.

In each appendage's terminal end exists a palm, with each palm possessing ten fingers. Notably, each hand exhibits a fractal structure — the finger of one hand serves as the appendages leading to another, and this pattern continues recursively, with the smallest tentacles being so delicate that they can only be observed under a microscope. Each hand is equipped with eleven tentacle-like suckers, one large sucker positioned centrally and ten additional suckers located where the fingers would typically terminate. These suckers are present on every hand of Qwerty, irrespective of their size.

If one gazes intently into the fog for a sufficient amount of time, they will observe that the lines etched on the nearby solid surfaces — including the one they are standing on — now display an identical pattern of lines and gaps. This pattern, which is the only one that can be deciphered, translates to "QWERTY C0MES" and is consistently oriented toward the fog. After a brief interval, Qwerty will materialize from the direction indicated by these lines and try to seize the individual who triggered its appearance. If successful, it will drag them down into the fog. Then the wanderers' destination becomes unknown.

Qwerty is completely immune to melee attacks such as slashing and stabbing with cold weapons, as well as brute-force unarmed assaults like striking and tearing — these cause it no damage and instead provoke it, causing it to expand its attack target to include all nearby wanderers. However, experiments have confirmed that heavy firearms such as guns, rocket launchers, and grenade launchers can effectively injure it. At the injury sites, a deep blue fluid oozes out, which rapidly evaporates upon contact with air, leaving no trace. It should be noted that Qwerty only ceases its attack and retreats into the misty sea when subjected to a fatal injury. Currently, nothing is known about how Qwerty heals its wounds.
