==Colonies and Outposts==
Due to the nature of '''Level 0.5''', it is impossible to create outposts within this level.

==Ingresses and Egresses==
All '''Level 0.5'''<nowiki/>'s ingresses and egresses are listed below:

===Ingresses===
The only known access to '''Level 0.5''' is through extremely rare specific "cutoffs" within [[Level 0]]. The appearance of a cutoff is drastically different from regular [[Level 0]] outcomes, manifesting as a straight hallway carpeted with yellow carpet, containing a large mirror approximately 3 meters high and spanning the width of the hallway. The mirror is not made of glass, but an unknown blue metal with a perfectly smooth, reflective surface that casts the wanderer’s reflection — one whose movements are delayed by nearly 0.5 seconds, showing an obvious lag effect relative to the wanderer’s own actions.

The mirror severs the hallway completely; no trace of [[Level 0]] can be seen behind it, only a deep, profound blue that matches the carpet color of '''Level 0.5'''. Any attempt to touch the mirror by hand, hurl objects at it, or walk directly through it will cause the wanderer to lose balance instantly, "sink" through the floor beneath their feet, and plummet into the space behind the mirror.

While falling, the wanderer will witness the surrounding scenery warp into a kaleidoscopic distortion: the yellow wallpaper and carpet of [[Level 0]] will gradually shatter into countless blue shards, which spin and rearrange to ultimately form the cubic structures and the sea of fog of '''Level 0.5'''. The duration of the fall is entirely random, lasting as short as 3 seconds or as long as several days. During this time, the wanderer will feel no gravity or physical discomfort, and their consciousness will be in a semi-lucid state, as if trapped in a dream. The fall ends the moment the wanderer’s feet touch the blue carpet of '''Level 0.5''', and their consciousness will snap back to full clarity immediately.

As of right now, it is believed these "cutoffs" occur when a "glitch" occurs within [[Level 0]], or a portion of it somehow noclips onto itself.

===Egresses===
No stable exits to '''Level 0.5''' have been found. Below are unconfirmed and unstable ones: several wanderers have reportedly been able to escape through a variety of means, such as finding an oddly colored pillar, falling asleep or floating in the fog for a long period of time; also, it is theorized that, if one travels far enough in this level, they will be transported back to [[Level 0]].

